rfolk, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Peter","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Peter Edisfield was born about 1140, in Edgefield, Norfolk, England, United Kingdom, his father, Humphrey de Edisfield, was 22 and his mother, Unknown, was 22. He had at least 2 sons with Maud Walcote."},"et":{"about 1140–":"umbes 1140–Surnud","1140–Male":"1140–Surnud","1142–Female":"1142–Surnud","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1120–Female":"1120–Surnud","about 1140":"umbes 1140","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","Edgefield, Norfolk, England":"Edgefield, Norfolk, England","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1140–":"noin 1140–Kuollut","1140–Male":"1140–Kuollut","1142–Female":"1142–Kuollut","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1120–Female":"1120–Kuollut","about 1140":"noin 1140","about 1170":"noin 1170","1120":"1120","1142":"1142","1140":"1140","1170":"1170","Edgefield, Norfolk, England":"Edgefield, Norfolk, England","Erpingham, Norfolk, England":"Erpingham, Norfolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuni